l automation systems.\n</p>\n<p>\nHere\'s a timeline of significant events to date in the history of ROS.  If you know of an event that we should, <a href=\"mailto:info@osrfoundation.org\">let us know</a>!\n</p>\n<!-- This shortcode call uses the VeriteCo TimelineS WordPress plugin -->\n[timeline src=\"https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/pub?key=0AuspqEoCc-R7dDNNdHVPSWJtZFVhcW93bUpfNTRWZVE&output=html\"]\n\n<!-- This iframe embed pulls the javascript from Knightlab\'s site -->\n<!--\n<iframe src=\'http://cdn.knightlab.com/libs/timeline/latest/embed/index.html?source=0AuspqEoCc-R7dDNNdHVPSWJtZFVhcW93bUpfNTRWZVE&font=Bevan-PotanoSans&maptype=toner&lang=en&start_at_slide=1&height=650\' width=\'100%\' height=\'650\' frameborder=\'0\'></iframe>\n-->\";}s:6:\"0iuqbm\";a:1:{s:15:\"textbox_content\";s:2526:\"<h2 class=\"widgettitle\">History</h2>\n<!-- This shortcode call uses the VeriteCo TimelineS WordPress plugin --><!--\n[timeline src=\"https://docs.google.com/spreadsheet/pub?key=0AuspqEoCc-R7dDNNdHVPSWJtZFVhcW93bUpfNTRWZVE&output=html\"]\n--><!-- This iframe embed pulls the javascript from Knightlab\'s site --><iframe src=\'https://cdn.knightlab.com/libs/timeline/latest/embed/index.html?source=0AuspqEoCc-R7dDNNdHVPSWJtZFVhcW93bUpfNTRWZVE&amp;font=Bevan-PotanoSans&amp;maptype=toner&amp;lang=en&amp;height=650&amp;start_at_end=true\' width=100% height=\'650\'></iframe>\n<p>\nROS is a large project with many ancestors and contributors. The need for an open-ended collaboration framework was felt by many people in the robotics research community, and many projects have been created towards this goal. \n</p><p>\nVarious efforts at Stanford University in the mid-2000s involving integrative, embodied AI, such as the STanford AI Robot (STAIR) and the Personal Robots (PR) program, created in-house prototypes of flexible, dynamic software systems intended for robotics use. In 2007, Willow Garage, a nearby visionary robotics incubator, provided significant resources to extend these